        public static final java.lang.String ARG_HOST
        An argument that specifies the host the task should run on. When set, this will be converted into a host-specific Request that will then run the task. jsl - Not sure when the class name prefix was added, but it's a good idea for this, but why the hell does it have to be the full path?
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ARG_RESUME_DATE

        public static final java.lang.String ARG_RESUME_DATE
        An argument that indiciates that the task schedule has been postponed. The value will be the utime representation of a java.util.Date. JobAdapter will prevent the task from running until this date has been reached.
